rComments: Really good and responsible prof, already my second course with her. Materials can be hard, but if you do all assignment and worksheet you will be fine on exams. She is inspirational on math, and it requires thinking for assignments. You will learn a lot with her if you do put time on the course.

I currently have B24 with her and I am enjoying it very much. She is not an easy professor. She treats mathematics very deeply and expects you to understand it deeply as well. If you want an easy pass, she is not the right prof but if you actually want to learn and willing to put the work (she askes for a lot) she is the one!

Currently have her. She is an amazing calc prof. She goes straight to the point and simplifies everything so everyone understands. If you put in the work you will do good. Exams are tough but to solve this try studying past exams (they are very similar!) I currently have around low 70s and trust me Im below average with a 80% received in HS calc

Her course workload is heavy as she has weekly tutorial quizzes and weekly exercises that take 4-8 hours to do. In lecture, she makes lots of mistakes and her writing is not the clearest either. She also goes quick in lecture, she will go over proof of theorems and examples in 3-5 minutes. She teaches more theory and does not provide many examples.

Camelia is really nice and seems to care about her students and their learning. Sometimes she rushes through stuff but slows down and explains things if you ask her, and does good review. Camelia is open to questions and corrections and is really smart but doesn't have too much of ego unlike some other professors. Make sure to do the exam review.
